Methods ib Java-block of code that performs certain actions.
Built-in methods string.length->returns the number of characters in a string.

Methods:
with parameters
Without paramethers
Paramethers VS Arguments?
Create a method to return the result of adding the numbers.

public double addNumbers(double num1, double num2) {
return num1+num2;
}
Must have parts in methods
1) return type (we can return any type primitive or non primitive, void)
2) Name of the method
3) Parameters/no parameters
Benefits of methods:
1) Reduce code duplication
2) More cleaner and manageable code
3) Save memory
4) Increases readability

Variables -----
Local variables
any variables that is declared inside the method or a block or a constructor is called a local variable